title: China’s new ambassador warns of ‘serious difficulties’ in relationship with U.S.
description: After a months-long delay, during a troubled period in relations between the two countries, the new Chinese ambassador Xie Feng arrived at JFK airport, hoping “to deepen exchanges and cooperation between China and the United States.”

title: China urges U.S. to ‘take practical actions’ on bilateral relations
description: China's foreign ministry is urging the U.S. to “take practical actions” to get relations between the countries “back on the right track.” Ministry spokesperson Mao Ning made the remarks in response to President Biden suggesting that a shift in U.S.-China relations could occur soon.

title: Royals reject calls to return body of 'stolen' prince taken to U.K. as a child after colonial raid
description: The British royal family has said it will not return the body of Ethiopia's Prince Alemayehu, captured by British troops, in the latest high-profile feud over the legacy of its brutal colonial past.

title: Rolf Harris, disgraced children's TV entertainer and convicted sex offender, dies at 93
description: Rolf Harris, the veteran entertainer whose decades-long career as a family favorite on British and Australian television was shattered when he was convicted of sexual assaults on young girls, has died.

title: Portuguese police resume search for missing British child Madeleine McCann
description: Portuguese police have resumed their search for Madeleine McCann, the British toddler who disappeared in the country’s Algarve region in 2007. Prosecutors in Germany, where the suspect is being held on separate charges, said “certain tips” led them to the reservoir about 30 miles from where the then-3-year-old was last seen.

title: Cars set on fire in Cardiff as UK police face 'large scale disorder' after road crash
description: Youths pelted police with objects and set cars and trash bins ablaze in Cardiff in unrest that erupted after two teens died in a road accident, officials said.

title: Portuguese police resume search for Madeleine McCann, British child missing since 2007
description: Portuguese police aided by German and British colleagues resumed the search for Madeleine McCann, the British child who disappeared in the country 16 years ago.

title: Prince Harry loses bid to challenge decision not to let him pay for U.K. police protection
description: Prince Harry on Tuesday lost a bid to legally challenge the British government’s decision not to allow him to pay for police protection while he is in the United Kingdom.

title: Russia alleges cross-border attack by Ukrainian saboteurs
description: Russian officials have claimed that Ukrainian military saboteurs launched a cross-border attack on a small village in the Belgorod region. Kyiv officials denied any link with the group and blamed the fighting on a revolt by disgruntled Russians against the Kremlin. Neither version of events could be independently verified in an area that has witnessed sporadic spillover since Russia’s invasion of Ukraine.

title: 4 people arrested on suspicion of hanging effigy of soccer star Vinícius off a bridge
description: Four people suspected of hanging an effigy of Real Madrid player Vinícius Júnior off a highway bridge in Madrid in January have been arrested, Spanish police said Tuesday.

title: Russia battles pro-Ukrainian incursion for 2nd day and reports more drone attacks
description: Russian troops and security forces fought for a second day Tuesday against an alleged cross-border raid that Moscow blamed on Ukrainian military saboteurs but which Kyiv portrayed as an uprising against the Kremlin by Russian partisans.

title: Sherpa guide Kami Rita scales Mount Everest for a record 28th time
description: Veteran Sherpa guide Kami Rita scaled Mount Everest for the 28th time Tuesday, beating his own record less than a week after setting it.

title: Australian Indigenous TV host quits program over racist backlash
description: Australian Indigenous journalist Stan Grant has quit in response to online racist abuse over his comments during King Charles III’s coronation.

title: Mexico’s Popocatépetl volcano spews ash, gas plumes into air
description: Mexico’s Popocatépetl volcano has disrupted air travel and raised concerns about evacuation as ash coats the area around the mountain.
